The service ruins everything about this place. I’ll start off by speaking very well about the food, as it is important that if you want good Indian food, you should know you won’t be disspaointed. However, our experience here was, by far, the absolute rudest I have ever experienced in the service industry. My friend brought us here for the food, we are not locals and could have gone anywhere. We were seated outside and and our server went through the menu with us very thoroughly. We placed our order; 2 appetizers, 3 alcoholic brevags, and 3 entrees. Our server was very awkward, but friendly. After we got our food he disappeared immediately, we didn’t even get refills on our drinks. After a while, he returns to pick up our table. THIS IS WHERE THINGS TURN...After finishing our food, we saw a sign that mentioned a buffet until 4pm; we ordered our food at 3pm. We mentioned to the server that we wish he would have told us about the buffet as it included free alcoholic drinks and a variety Of options (including someone of the food we ordered). HIS RESPONSE, “well, why do I have to tell you, there’s a sign, that’s what’s signs are for” We were taken away, as we were not rude, just explaining we wish we would have known. The best part of this is when he goes even further to tell us how amazing the buffet is and that it would have been a better deal, but we should have read the sign. We asked to speak to the owner, who told is THE EXACT SAME THING. For the record, we know very well he wasn’t the owner, but the son of the owner acting as the owner, but we didn’t want to pursue this any further. We paid our bill and left, never coming back. HORRIFIC SERVICE OUTWEIGHS AMAZING FOOD.

We ordered delivery. 3 nonveg, 4 veg, 2 appetizers, various breads The delivery arrived on the dot, and the food was hot -- that is where we give some stars  Unfortunately, we could not get excited about any of the dishes or the sauces. We had ordered the dishes medium hot except one hot. The spice level (heat) was there, but the food itself was tasteless, almost as if the food sits there cooked and then you add the spices at the end and off you go. The breads were hot (good), but the Naans, parathas and pooris were all tough and difficult to cut. Not sure why. Chicken tikka dry Shrimp do payyazi was hard to describe -- did not taste fresh Okra -- not what I expected -- was wet not stir or skillet fry saag paneer - very bland = tasteless kobi aloo matar == some peas were like stones - hard partially cooked; cauliflower was there -but very small florets and not much of them chana masaala = ok but not great banana pakora = ended up being left after a bite on almost all plates sahani -- this was a new one for us - had some flavor dal poori - and coconut poori -- were tough but also tasted of either old oil or some oil we are not familiar with  We were excited that there was a new Indian restaurant in our neighborhood, but regret that we will most likely not try it again. It could be that this is just a completely different style of India than we know or expect and that explains why so many people like it.

Just enjoyed a wonderful evening at Clove. I was researching Indian restaurants around my area and came across this place! The service was fantastic and so was my waiter. This friendly man was very helpful when describing each dish. So lets get started! First, I started with the tandoori chicken wings as my appetizer...they were super yummy...especially with the raita (cucumber/yogurt sauce). Next, I had the chicken tikka masala...this was one of the best I've had. Perfect balance of cream and tomato mix to the sauce and  it wasn't overly spicy, (like other kinds I've had). The chicken was really tender and the rice was seasoned just right. I also had their garlic naan. Words cannot describe how amazing this bread was! It was soft and yet it had a little crunch. Not overly garlicky...and had a sweet taste as well. My taste buds were overwhelmed with all the flavors! Last, I had 2 of their deserts listed. Rasmalai was the first one. I was interested in it because it said it was a cheese ball served with a sweet sauce. The texture was really different...in a good way! The sauce went great with them.  The firni was the last thing I tasted from this excellent restaurant. I'm a big fan of rice pudding and this one was definitely one of my top favorites! The little sprinkle of coconut shavings on top, really pulled it together with the creamy cinnamon flavors.  Overall, I enjoyed my meal and service at Clove...I'll definitely go back!!
I visit often with friends and coworkers. Delicious food, great customer service. Definitely recommend this place.
Overpriced, taste is good but average, there's nothing special about the taste to justify the prices. Also the portions sizes are extremely small.
Food was dry and not flavorful. Buffet had fewer options than comparable places.

Had been there on a Sunday morning Ordered Biryani on the suggestion of the owner(maybe) on a spicy scale The rice used was just normal left over and just a couple of basmati rice strands in between and it was just filled with chili sauce.. Had chole Bhaji as appetizer and who gives just one puri for the appetizer? Horrible horrible I'm a good cook I know how biryani should taste this biryani was just some chili yellow rice with some veggies and one small bay leaf broken into five pieces!!!! Avoid going there total rip off.
Excellent service. The food was great as well. Enjoyed our time.
Poor service to black customers. They are racist if you ask me.

Food was good. Had some trouble with the payment: we'd split the bill three ways, but they took out the entire amount from my account. Of course, it got fixed, but not until after I called them up and mentioned it. The samosas are pretty good.
Love the food here.
Tried the buffet lunch @$10.95, its actually really good. The rice pudding's a very nice finish. Service's excellent too

Ordered take out from this restaurant, and the food did not disappoint. Very friendly staff as well. The samosas are some of the better ones I've had from different Indian restaurants that I've been to.
Such a great deal for the lunch buffet. Dinner fair is great try the peanut chicken.
Nice location, can eat by the street as well. Buffet is pretty good, very friendly waiters, food is average

I was so excited and happy to find a place has good price and reviews in NYC. Then the reality hit.  Buffet lunch for 10, good price? Yes yes it does come with a harsh service and 4 things to choose from with naan and samosa, rice.  The service girl in green was having an off day, as the lady next to me said when she saw I got bad service. The green shirt lady sever jumped in front of me when I'm getting food, then she looked at me and said: "oh you want this?? Fine, you go." I was like, well, I have been in line getting food, but thank you for your generosity to let me get food I'm paying for.  Then 10 minutes later (I usually take my time at buffet to enjoy food and peace) she came to my table and take the white water bottle and slammed it back down, I'm not sure if she was just checking to see if the bottle is empty, it's clear glass bottle so there is more than half water left, maybe water is hard to see... And before that, about my first plate, she came with a check slammed on my table, slammed the salt and pepper down to hold the check.... I started to think maybe this is just how she does things. So I laughed off and move on.  Food: it is not that great. I am in computer science field so yes I know how to judge Indians food since most of my friends are Indians. This is not what good food taste like, chicken was extremely dry wth sauce, shrimp is shrunk to the smallest and sauce is not creamy and tasty as regular paneer.  Samosa is ok, super small with little filling.  Ok I'm done complaining  lol anyway, I'm sad that I was fooled but oh well, NYC, I'm experiencing it.  The clear glass bottle ... But the server can't see water in it so slamming it down the table helped her know 😂slamming table is the new norm in service here 😻
To be fair, they have pretty tasty food. The lunch buffet is great, and they give you a glass of their homemade Indian iced tea (no refills). But overall decent food.
Excellent food and everyone is very friendly.
This place has awakened in me a love of Indian cuisine. It's become a regular spot for my wife and I to escape to. Great food, awesome staff, and a lunch buffet for under $12.
This is one of these best Indian restaurants in New York City. Always start your meal at Clove with the banana pakora...they're sublime!
Went there for their lunch buffet, i was amazed by their hospitality. The food was okay

The food and service was exceptional. The chef came out to meet my friend and I and was extremely warm. The meat was tender and I truly enjoyed the experience! Will definitely be coming back and recommending to friends! Make sure to try the chicken and veggie samosas.
Authentic Indian cuisine, great service at an inexpensive  price!
Super yummy and really attentive to detail! Really unique flair to Indian food. The homemade tea is amazing.
I went for the first time last night. Excellent service and the food is amazing. You could tell it is authentic home style cooking.
Great food

This place is beyond great. The food was wonderful, but what really stood out was the service. By far the best service I have ever had. The staff went out of their way to accommodate us. Definitely will return.

I just finished my take out dinner, and it was delicious! I got a tandoori dinner for one: switched tandoori to chicken & veggies curry, veggie samosa, cheese naan, lentil soup and mango ice cream. The food was fantastic, loved every one of the dishes. I wish I had more time to dine in-the place looked really nice, may be next time. Overall, give five stars, keep up the good job!

Their food is authentic and delicious. Their lunch buffet is absolutely amazing, especially when they serve Gulab Jamun. The service is very good and the owner is incredibly friendly. I hope to see them succeed. It's become one of my favorite weekly destinations.
The lunch buffet is fantastic. I like the ice tea.
yum
I ordered a cup of tea to go,  they gave my tea in a plastic soup container instead of tea cup.  😡😡
Awesome Indian food,  unique atmosphere and great service,  u could not recommend this place enough if you like Indian food

My first time visiting Clove was very pleasant. I passed by a numerous number of times, but once I entered the resturant, the gloomy rainy day melted away. The atmosphere is calming and the food delicious. The staff are wonderful and courteous. If you haven't been but are in the area you should swing by.
Food is always great!

Their food are to die for (in a goood way). My first time trying out Indian food and i have to say that it is a MUST go for anyone who hasnt been here. I will be going again. The staff are amazing people who really know how to take care of their guest.

My family and I come here and also order from here A lot! We love them. We love the Decor, owners and  their families and especially the food of course. Everything tastes great to us. We have been waiting for this place to open up for a while now and now that it has i wish i wasn't working as far from this place as i am right now because i would literally be eating lunch here almost everyday. Their breads are amazing, their sauces are great, samosas are awesome and their tea is delicious. Great addition to the neighborhood and Kid friendly which i love and appreciate! See you soon Clove!
The service was great, and the food was delicious.

I visited the resturant yesterday welcome by a lay back environment and a nice decor.  After looking though the many of options (which is always a great thing) I finally order the samosas, nan, and lamb vindaloo.  The food came out very quick and was very good.  The green basil sauce on the table was very good and was a great compliment to my meal.  At first I was worry from the food portion that it was not going to be enough, but i was over stuff by time I left... And trust I'm a big boy.  One of the staff members heard me over talking about how I like really spicy food .. It turned out to be the owner who then went to the back and brought me out some home made hotsauce.  It  was spicier than average hot sauce but not really hot like I am use to having from Indian resturants.  However he did inform me that he had to cool it down as many guest could not enjoy the level of spice it was once at.  It was awesome to see a owner who was still able to be down to earth and still able to serve food and make time to talk to guest.  Will I be there again??? yes!!! It's a great edition to Harlem and the food was great.  Be sure to ask for the home made house sauce if you dare 👀
The crab curry, seekh kebab and coconut puri are reliably delicious. This is the best Indian food I've been able to find in Manhattan north of Murray Hill.

The restaurant has a great vibe and decor. My personal taste test for all Indian restaurants is the samosa. In my experience, if you can nail the samosa, the rest of the menu is usually on point too. So, I came in and tried and the appetizer sampler. The taste was there in the stuffing but the samosa crust could afford to be a bit more flakier and less doughy. Their sauces were on point though. Hope to see this restaurant grow and succeed.

I went for a lunch buffet. It was average food. Nothing special. So I went back to try their regular menu. I ordered Paneer Makhani. It was the most horrible Indian food I've ever had. Basically, paneer (Indian cottage cheese) cubes were dipped in sugary water with tamarind flavor. The dish was so sweet, I couldn't taste anything. It's supposed to be creamy, but there was no cream in it whatsoever. Also, I don't think the chef has any idea whatsoever how to make the dish. I'm never going back again. Really bad quality of Indian food! I'm Indian and I've never had so bad food before. What a waste of my $18! I ordered garlic naan as well, which was okay. I don't know who these "majority of guests" are but I don't think I'm going back. Not interested in having sugary syrup again.

Friendly atmosphere, great food!! A must if you've never eaten Indian cuisine but wanted you try it.. Let the staff suggest a few meals, I promise you won't be disappointed.. I'm definitely returning...  Thanks again for the hospitality!

The staff is super friendly and attentive.  We had the buffet (very inexpensive) which was mainly vegetarian with some meat dishes as well.  Food was delicious and their homemade hot sauce was perfect.  Definitely recommend and will return.
Very friendly service and good authentic Indian food
